        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="4">
            <title>Service procedure</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To avoid property damage, personal injury, or death, park the vehicle on a flat level surface,
                        set the parking brake, turn the engine off, and chock the wheels.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the fuse panel cover.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove heater trim panel (Figure 1, Item 1).</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the blower housing (Figure 1, Item 2) and disconnect the blower harness
                    connector.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0616031" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/g0616031.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="502px"
                         scalefitheight="328px"/>
                <caption>Figure 1. Exploded View of Blower Housing</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Heater Trim Panel</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Blower Housing</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate the foam water vent as shown in Figure 2, Item 1.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0616032" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/g0616032.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="392px"
                         scalefitheight="328px"/>
                <caption>Figure 2. Blower Housing Side View</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Foam Vent</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Drain Tube</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Use an Exacto knife to cut as much of the foam vent away as possible and carefully
                    remove the foam pieces with long nose pliers. Make sure all foam pieces are removed to prevent
                    blockage in the drain tube.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the duck-bill vent (Figure 3) into the drain tube (Figure 4). Apply pressure to
                    the duck-bill vent to seat it into the drain tube.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0616033" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/g0616033.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="208px"/>
                <caption>Figure 3. Duck-bill Vent</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0616034" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G0616034.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="352px"
                         scalefitheight="328px"/>
                <caption>Figure 4. Blower Housing with Duck-bill</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Duck-bill Vent Inserted Into Drain Tube</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Re-install the blower housing, reconnect the blower harness connector, and re-install
                    the heater trim panel and fuse panel.
                </para>
            </step1>
